body:
The point of this pull request is to switch from using the older <Jet Type>CorrectionProducers to using the newer Corrected<JetType>Producers. The older producers are not thread safe and do not use the consumes features. At some point there was a push to switch to the newer producers (see [1]), but we think that some of the code was overlooked. This brings the "new" python files fully in sync and will be a big help to anyone who directly uses the jet correctors.

[1]: https://twiki.cern.ch/twiki/bin/view/CMSPublic/FWMultithreadedConsumesJetCorrectorMigration

@rappoccio
